{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:proverbs.6",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 6,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 6 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.6.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:1",
      "text": "My son, if thou be surety for thy friend, thou hast engaged fast thy hand to a stranger,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.6.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:2",
      "text": "Thou art ensnared with the words of thy mouth, and caught with thy own words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.6.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:3",
      "text": "Do, therefore, my son, what I say, and deliver thyself: because thou art fallen into the hand of thy neighbour. Run about, make haste, stir up thy friend:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.6.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:4",
      "text": "Give not sleep to thy eyes, neither let thy eyelids slumber.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.6.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:5",
      "text": "Deliver thyself as a doe from the hand, and as a bird from the hand of the fowler.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.6.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:6",
      "text": "Go to the ant, O sluggard, and consider her ways, and learn wisdom:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.6.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:7",
      "text": "Which, although she hath no guide, nor master, nor captain,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.6.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:8",
      "text": "Provideth her meat for herself in the summer, and gathereth her food in the harvest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.6.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:9",
      "text": "How long wilt thou sleep, O sluggard? when wilt thou arise out of thy sleep?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.6.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:10",
      "text": "Thou wilt sleep a little, thou wilt slumber a little, thou wilt fold thy hands a little to sleep:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.6.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:11",
      "text": "And want shall come upon thee, as a traveller, and poverty as a man armed. But if thou be diligent, thy harvest shall come as a fountain, and want shall flee far from thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.6.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:12",
      "text": "A man that is an apostate, an unprofitable man, walketh with a perverse mouth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.6.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:13",
      "text": "He winketh with the eyes, presseth with the foot, speaketh with the finger.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.6.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:14",
      "text": "With a wicked heart he deviseth evil, and at all times he soweth discord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.6.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:15",
      "text": "To such a one his destruction shall presently come, and he shall suddenly be destroyed, and shall no longer have any remedy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.6.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:16",
      "text": "Six things there are, which the Lord hateth, and the seventh his soul detesteth:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.6.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:17",
      "text": "Haughty eyes, a lying tongue, hands that shed innocent blood,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.6.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:18",
      "text": "A heart that deviseth wicked plots, feet that are swift to run into mischief,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.6.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:19",
      "text": "A deceitful witness that uttereth lies, and him that soweth discord among brethren.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.6.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:20",
      "text": "My son, keep the commandments of thy father, and forsake not the law of thy mother.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.6.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:21",
      "text": "Bind them in thy heart continually, and put them about thy neck.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.6.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:22",
      "text": "When thou walkest, let them go with thee: when thou sleepest, let them keep thee, and when thou awakest, talk with them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.6.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:23",
      "text": "Because the commandment is a lamp, and the law a light, and reproofs of instruction are the way of life:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.6.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:24",
      "text": "That they may keep thee from the evil woman, and from the flattering tongue of the stranger.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.6.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:25",
      "text": "Let not thy heart covet her beauty, be not caught with her winks:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.6.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:26",
      "text": "For the price of a harlot is scarce one loaf: but the woman catcheth the precious soul of a man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.6.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:27",
      "text": "Can a man hide fire in his bosom, and his garments not burn?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.6.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:28",
      "text": "Or can he walk upon hot coals, and his feet not be burnt?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.6.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:29",
      "text": "So he that goeth in to his neighbour's wife, shall not be clean when he shall touch her.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.6.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:30",
      "text": "The fault is not so great when a man hath stolen: for he stealeth to fill his hungry soul:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.6.31",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:31",
      "text": "And if he be taken, he shall restore sevenfold, and shall give up all the substance of his house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.6.32",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:32",
      "text": "But he that is an adulterer, for the folly of his heart shall destroy his own soul:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.6.33",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:33",
      "text": "He gathereth to himself shame and dishonour, and his reproach shall not be blotted out:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.6.34",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:34",
      "text": "Because the jealousy and rage of the husband will not spare in the day of revenge,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.6.35",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:35",
      "text": "Nor will he yield to any man's prayers, nor will he accept for satisfaction ever so many gifts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
